threats and force companies to install pollution controls. At a time when 
members of poor and/or minority communities are objecting to being stuck with 
disproportionate numbers of waste sites, the authors hope to convert readers 
into activists by demonstrating that they can successfully oppose powerful 
corporate interests. 
