<HEADLINE>
<P>
STYLE: A DESIGNER PORTFOLIO; FASHION, ANTI-FASHION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Produced and styled by Michael Eisenhower 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fall fashions reflected cloistered living, modesty, a sense of atonement. But 
this spring, some designers celebrate youthful innocence via baby-doll and 
tomboy styles.Others embrace ethnic, neo-punk and deconstructivist looks. What 
does this say about the clothes we'll eventually be wearing? That they're 
light, sheer, very short or very long, shiny, sometimes pretty but more often 
not. This season, it seems, no one wants to dress up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
