POP MUSIC CHARTS: THE POWER OF 'COLOUR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Celine Dion, often put in the same vocal league with Mariah Carey, has 
blossomed into such a commercial force that she's performing like Carey on the 
charts too -- topping both of The Times' Southern California pop charts. Dion's 
"The Colour of My Love" is the No. 1 album and her "The Power of Love" is the 
leading single. One of the surprise hits of the year -- receiving an early 
boost from KROQ exposure -- is Us3's "Cantaloop," which is not only No. 9 on 
the local chart but No. 7 nationally. When it first came out, few thought the 
jazz/rap single would get much major airplay. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,42,11 Title, 
