<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMING UP ROSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for Dan Berger's article on wine pricing (Restaurant News, Feb. 6).I 
have long since given up paying $30 in a restaurant for a wine that I can drink 
at home for $8. At a restaurant I would rather buy a single glass of wine and 
nurse it through the whole meal than to be coerced into paying exorbitant 
markups. 
</P>
<P>
 I have noted the restaurants Berger identifies as adding an eminently fair 
charge of $8 to $10 a bottle. Please list more. I am looking forward, again, to 
having a bottle of wine with my restaurant meal. 
</P>
<P>
 MICHAEL ZAPF 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
