<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT IF THERE WERE NO MOTHERS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In class at Barnard College five years ago, my daughter was defending an 
unpopular cause -- motherhood.So unworthy are we mothers, it seemed, that her 
professor sneered his ultimate insult: She probably wanted to grow up to be 
"just like her mother." 
</P>
<P>
 "The Trials of Lawyer Moms" (Feb. 21) was an intelligent article on a group of 
Washington lawyer-mothers who described some of the trials of juggling two 
full-time careers. Yet even this sympathetic piece said that joining the group 
"eased the stigma of going from legal eagle to mommy hen." 
</P>
<P>
 I am so tired of hearing mothers referred to as second-class citizens. Has 
anyone made it into this world without one? 
</P>
<P>
 D. SPIGELMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
