<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; EDUCATION: FUNERAL HELD FOR AWARD-WINNING TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Funeral services were held Thursday for Ron Brown, a 21-year teacher at Horace 
Mann Elementary School in Beverly Hills who was hailed as one of the district's 
most talented and popular teachers. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, a social studies instructor, was 51.The cause of death was not 
disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown was named the Beverly Hills Education Foundation teacher of the year in 
1992. He taught at Weigand Elementary in Los Angeles before going to Horace 
Mann. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was an outstanding teacher, and the students and staff loved him," 
Principal Arthur Field said. "He was kind and caring, and did all he could to 
help when a student had a problem." 
</P>
<P>
 Brown graduated from Los Angeles High School and USC. He is survived by a son, 
Chris, a brother, David, and sister Phyllis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
