<P>
DEPORTATION BEATS INCARCERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * After attending a neighborhood meeting with the Santa Ana city manager and a 
Santa Ana police captain as guest speakers, I find the (City Council vote) for 
a new Santa Ana jail is treating the symptom and not the cause. 
</P>
<P>
 Former Immigration and Naturalization Service Western Regional Commissioner 
Harold Ezell has stated at least 50% of Santa Ana arrests are (of) illegal 
immigrants. 
</P>
