<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 General Manager Neil Smith of the New York Rangers said he has signed U.S. 
defenseman Barry Richter and will assign him to Binghamton, N.Y., of the 
American Hockey League.He also intends to sign center Todd Marchant. 
</P>
<P>
 "With his speed, he's got a chance," Smith said. "I think we can make a 
checker out of him." 
</P>
<P>
 However, Smith said he's not interested in signing Peter or Chris Ferraro, 
even though Peter was the Olympic team's top goal scorer in pre-tournament 
play. The Ferraros' size -- each twin is 5 feet 10 and 175 pounds -- makes them 
questionable pro prospects. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
