<P>
PREP BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; CRESCENTA VALLEY UPSETS SANTA ANA VALLEY, 69-67 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley High pulled off one of the biggest upsets in the boys' 
basketball playoffs with a 69-67 victory over The Times' No. 16-ranked team, 
Santa Ana Valley, in a Southern Section Division I-AA semifinal game Saturday 
night at Glendale High. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley (19-9) outrebounded fourth-seeded Santa Ana Valley, 36-11. 
Blake Jacobson led the way with 13 rebounds, despite being called for his third 
foul early in the second quarter. He added 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons will play Long Beach Poly for the championship Saturday night at 
Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 10 Long Beach Poly 61, Long Beach Wilson 43 -- In a game between Moore 
League foes, Poly (24-6) won for the third time over Wilson (22-8), this time 
in the Southern Section Division I-AA semifinals Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 At Long Beach City College, Damion Dawson scored 16 points and James Brown 
added 13 for Poly. GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 No. 3 Mission Hills Alemany 67, Hacienda Heights Los Altos 32 -- Zevette 
Mitchell scored 16 points and Kelly McKay had 10 steals to lead Alemany (26-0) 
over Los Altos (18-11) in II-A quarterfinal at La Canada St. Francis High. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 4 Ventura Buena 61, San Clemente 34 -- Mikko Giordano scored 16 points and 
grabbed 13 rebounds to lead top-seeded Buena (23-2) over San Clemente (21-6) in 
a I-A semifinal at Oxnard Rio Mesa High. Michelle Macintyre led San Clemente 
with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 6 Palos Verdes Peninsula 60, San Gabriel 38 -- Mimi McKinney scored 20 
points and had seven rebounds to lead Peninsula (24-3) over San Gabriel (22-5) 
in a I-AA semifinal at South Torrance High. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 43, No. 16 Newbury Park 41 -- Gina Heads made two free throws 
with 12 seconds to play to lift Newport Harbor (22-6) in a III -- AA semifinal 
at Camarillo High. 
</P>
<P>
 Heads, who had made only two of seven free throws before the fourth quarter, 
tied the game, 41-41, with a foul shot with 2:38 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park finished 23-5. 
</P>
