<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wetlands tours -- Guided public tours of the Bolsa Chica wetlands will be held 
Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 The tours, sponsored by Amigos de Bolsa Chica, will depart from the wetlands' 
ecological reserve every 20 minutes beginning at 9 a.m. The last tour will 
depart at 10:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Chica is one of the best bird-watching sites in the county, attracting a 
variety of shorebirds and land birds.Birds likely to be seen on the tours 
include egrets, loons, herons, grebes and other waterfowl. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who would like to take a tour are asked to meet at the Bolsa Chica 
Ecological Reserve's building on Pacific Coast Highway, about half a mile south 
of Warner Avenue. It is across from Bolsa Chica State Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea field trip -- The Sea & Sage chapter of the National Audubon Society will 
hold a pelagic field trip Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The trip begins at 6:30 a.m. It is the second in a series of such trips 
sponsored by the chapter. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will go out on the 40-foot Sea Scout from Newport Harbor and take a 
triangular route out to the tip of Catalina Island. 
</P>
<P>
 It is the best time of year to see albatross, chapter officials said, and the 
group will also see many other species of sea birds. 
</P>
<P>
 The trip is limited to 25 people and advance reservations are required. The 
cost for the trip is $25. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants should bring binoculars (but not scopes for this type of 
bird-watching), food and warm clothing. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the chapter office at (714) 261-7963. 
</P>
</TEXT>
