<HEADLINE>
<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Finland shut out Russia for the second time, 4-0, Saturday night to win the 
bronze medal.Their only other Olympic hockey medal was a silver in 1988.  
</P>
<P>
 For the first time, the Russians came away empty handed. 
</P>
<P>
 In their 10 previous Olympics as the Soviet Union and Unified Team, they won 
eight gold medals, one silver and one bronze. They were never shut out and had 
a 60-6-2 record. This year's team finished at 4-4, including a 5-0 shutout by 
Finland in the second preliminary-round game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
