'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Germany took an early lead, hit every target at the shooting range and cruised 
to its second consecutive gold medal in the men's biathlon relay. 
</P>
<P>
 Ricco Gross, Frank Luck, Mark Kirchner and Sven Fischer finished the 
30-kilometer race in 1 hour 30 minutes 22.1 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Russians were second in the ski-and-shoot event, 61.5 seconds behind, and 
France was third, 2:09.2 behind. 
</P>
