<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; ARIZONA'S STOUDAMIRE ANSWERS CROWD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It wasn't all that warm a homecoming for Damon Stoudamire, so he decided to 
answer rudeness with rudeness. 
</P>
<P>
 Stoudamire, who played high school ball up the road in Portland, was booed 
every time he touched the ball in the first half at Eugene, Ore., then made the 
go-ahead basket with 45 seconds to play in ninth-ranked Arizona's 75-71 victory 
Saturday over Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
 Khalid Reeves hit two free throws with nine seconds to play to clinch the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Stoudamire broke a 71-71 tie with 53 seconds to play, driving the length of 
the court and hitting a jump shot. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were going to run a play, but it was my option to take it all the way," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 He had led all scorers with 13 first-half points. 
</P>
<P>
 "Every time the crowd got loud, the coach (Lute Olson) would call the play for 
me," Stoudamire said. "He did it a couple of times, and I was able to hit the 
shots when we needed them." 
</P>
<P>
 Stoudamire finished with 21 points. Reeves had 25, including seven of 
Arizona's last 11. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the sixth consecutive victory for the Wildcats (23-4, 12-3). Oregon 
fell to 9-14, 5-9. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona St. 80, Oregon St. 60 -- Stevin Smith had 22 points and Mario Bennett 
scored 19 to lead the Sun Devils at Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona State (13-11, 8-7) never trailed, but there were six ties early before 
Bennett hit a free throw and two rebound baskets to start a 10-0 run to a 27-17 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The last-place Beavers dropped to 6-17, 2-12. 
</P>
<P>
 Kareem Anderson led Oregon State with 20 points, 17 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington St. 75, Washington 51 -- Fred Ferguson scored 17 points and 
freshman Nathan Erdmann added a career-high 16 in his first start to lead the 
Cougars at Pullman, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Hill and Mark Hendrickson added 10 apiece as Washington State (17-9, 
7-7) gave Coach Kelvin Sampson his 100th victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Maurice Woods had 18 points to lead Washington (5-18, 3-11). 
</P>
