<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREED KEEPS CANYON OAKS PROPOSAL ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The opinion piece by Alexander Cockburn ("Speculation vs. Democracy in 
Topanga," Feb. 3) succinctly describes the situation Topangans have faced for 
16 years.A grandiose real estate scheme would destroy the headwaters of Topanga 
Creek and a beautiful valley. 
</P>
<P>
 This project does not fit any of the 10 goals of the area plan and is opposed 
by the vast majority of our canyon residents. 
</P>
<P>
 It is unfathomable to me that such an urban-style development could even be 
considered for this rural and mountainous terrain. It is greed that keeps this 
project alive, and damned be the land, the animals, the plants, the people who 
live there or future generations. 
