<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEADS' UP PLAY WINS FOR NEWPORT HARBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gina Heads got warm just in time on a cold Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 In fact, 12 seconds later would have been too late for the Newport Harbor 
girls' basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Heads was three for nine from the free-throw line before making two foul shots 
in the waning moments to help the Sailors sink Newbury Park, 43-41, in a 
Southern Section Division III-AA semifinal at Camarillo High. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor (22-6) plays Brea-Olinda in Saturday's final. 
</P>
<P>
 Heads made only two of seven free throws before the fourth quarter. She tied 
the game, 41-41, by converting one of two free throws with 2:38 left. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think I was a little stiff in the beginning and my shots were flat," said 
Heads, who finished with seven points. "I wasn't getting up on my toes." 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park (23-5) led throughout the first half and held a 30-23 advantage 
at the break. Newport Harbor held the Panthers scoreless for the first 3:58 and 
the final 4:06. 
</P>
<P>
 Genevieve Evarts led the Sailors on a 7-0 run to tie the score, 30-30, in the 
third period and nailed a 12-foot jumper at 2:18 to give Newport Harbor its 
first lead of the game, 34-33. MIKE GLAZE 
</P>
</TEXT>
