<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION IV-AA GIRLS' SEMIFINALS; DESPITE ROBINSON, SANTA YNEZ BEATS COSTA MESA 
IN OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID FELTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa senior Heather Robinson played an outstanding game, but Santa Ynez 
was a little better. 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson scored 36 points, 19 in the second half, but missed a free throw with 
10 seconds left that would have given the Mustangs a one-point lead. 
</P>
<P>
 In overtime, Robinson fouled out without scoring a point as the Pirates went 
on to an 83-75 overtime victory in a Southern Section Division IV-AA semifinal 
Saturday at Lompoc High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates (24-4) led by as many as 12 points in the second quarter (35-23) 
and by nine (51-42) with 5:07 left to play. 
</P>
<P>
 But Robinson almost single-handedly brought Costa Mesa (19-7) back. She scored 
12 third-quarter points, including a three-pointer that brought the Mustangs to 
within 55-54. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth, baskets by Robinson and Erin Brown again cut the Pirates' lead 
to 69-68. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ynez's Kacie Scoggin was fouled with 10 seconds remaining, but missed 
the front end of a one-and-one situation. Robinson grabbed the rebound and was 
immediately fouled by Kristi Rohr, who had 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 71-70, Robinson who had made all seven free throws until then, made 
the first but missed the second, forcing overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ynez will play its sixth consecutive IV-AA final and second in a row 
against Playa del Rey St. Bernard. DAVID FELTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
