<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUENA ROMPS PAST SAN CLEMENTE, 61-34 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Clemente couldn't stop Ventura Buena's inside game, as the host Bulldogs 
rolled to a 61-34 victory in a Southern Section Division I-A semifinal game 
Saturday at Rio Mesa High. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena (23-2), top-seeded in the division, will play Mater Dei in Saturday's 
final.The Tritons finish 21-6, their best season. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente trailed, 19-9, after one quarter and at halftime, 35-21. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tritons closed the gap to 13 points, at 37-24, but Buena closed the 
quarter with a 15-1 run to take a 52-25 lead after three quarters to put the 
game away. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are just a very good team," San Clemente Coach Mary Mulligan said. "They 
are big, physical and very solid. I thought we did a pretty good job 
defensively, but we just couldn't score." 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Macintyre led San Clemente with 14 points, and Shawna Waldner added 
11. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena center Mikko Giordano led all scorers with 16 points and pulled down 13 
rebounds, and backup center Nicole Greathouse added 13 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
