<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION III-A GIRLS' SEMIFINALS; FRESHMAN RESERVE LEADS SAN LUIS OBISPO PAST 
ESTANCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC BURDICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Luis Obispo reserve freshman center Yolanda White scored 18 points and 
grab 14 rebounds, leading the Tigers to a 50-42 victory over Estancia in a 
Division III-A playoff girls' game Saturday night at Cuesta College. 
</P>
<P>
 San Luis Obispo (17-10) advances into the championship game Saturday against 
Northern League rival Lompoc. 
</P>
<P>
 San Luis Obispo scored the first 11 points of the second quarter to break an 
8-8 tie and never trailed afterward. San Luis Obispo led at the break, 24-14. 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia, which finished 21-5, closed the gap to four points late in the third 
quarter on a three-pointer by Jenny Jennings. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Eagles got no closer. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennings and Laura Czingula each scored 12 points for Estancia. No other 
Eagles scored in double figures. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaymee Muriset had 10 points also for San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles were outrebounded, 37-18, and shot only 37% from the floor (16 of 
43). 
</P>
<P>
 "We executed well, we just missed a lot of shots we normally make," Estancia 
Coach Rich Boyce said. "Our girls gutted it out, but it was just not meant to 
be." 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia, which tied for second in the Pacific Coast League, upset 
third-seeded Rancho Alamitos, 51-44, Wednesday in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia had beaten Bellflower, 63-60, in the first round Feb. 19. ERIC 
BURDICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
