<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' TRACK AND FIELD / 1994 PREVIEW; WOODBRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: George Varvas (13th year). 
</P>
<P>
 1992-93: Fifth at the Orange County Championships, fourth in the Sea View 
League finals, 6-1 league dual meet record. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Wendy Brown, Sr., HJ; Angela Burgess, Jr., SP, DT; Julie 
Snyder, Jr., 800, 1600; Meisha Wilson-Duval, Jr., 100, 200, 400. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Frannie Simmons, So., 400; Erin Stovall, Fr., LJ. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: A team that isn't hoping for a repeat of last season. After finishing 
fifth at the Orange County championships and 6-1 in its Sea View League dual 
meets, the loss of Wilson-Duval to injury before league finals spelled the 
quick demise of the Warriors. The talented sprinter was the county runner-up in 
the 100 (12.75 wind-aided) and 200 (25.68 wind-aided) as well as third in the 
400 (59.74). Burgess, one of the standouts on the Warriors' outstanding 
basketball team, finished third in the discus at the Orange County 
championships and fourth in the shotput. Brown tied for fourth in the county 
high jump, and Stovall is one of Varvas' diamonds in the rough in the long 
jump. Simmons and Snyder will solidify the middle-distance races for the 
Warriors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
