<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' TRACK AND FIELD / 1994 PREVIEW; EDISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Karen O'Bric (fourth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1992-93: Sunset League champion, 7-0 in league dual meets. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Erin Bailey, Sr., 800; Sonya Bryant, So., SP, DT; Janndee 
Evans, Sr., 1600; Jeannie Formosa, Jr., 1600, 3200; Jennifer Formosa, Jr., 
1600, 3200; Suzanne Gates, Jr., HJ; Sara Griffiths, Sr., SP, DT; Elyse 
Homberger, Jr., 3200; Shauna Itri, So., 800, 1600; Julie Koudelka, Sr., 400; 
Tami Letterman, Jr., 100, 200; Kelly Marshall, So., 400; Kerry O'Bric, So., LJ, 
TJ, 300 IH; Marie Philman, So., 100 LH, DT, SP, HJ; Carrie Quinn, Sr., 800, 
1600. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Karen Anderson, So., 400; Kerrie Wright, Jr., 1600, 3200. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: As deep a team as there is anywhere (102 girls showed up the first 
day of practice a year ago), the Chargers show no signs of letting loose their 
hold on the Sunset League. Philman and O'Bric, the leaders of the girls' 
basketball team, cover the field events and hurdles while Letterman and 
Marshall head the sprint corps. Homberger was fifth in the State 3200 meters 
last year. The State Division II champion cross-country team will only help on 
the track. 
</P>
</TEXT>
