<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; RANCHO SANTIAGO POUNDS ORANGE COAST IN CONFERENCE 
OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Minici had a home run and three doubles to help Rancho Santiago to a 
15-3 victory over visiting Orange Coast in the Orange Empire Conference 
baseball opener Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Minici's three doubles tied a Rancho Santiago single-game record. The Dons 
also tied a team record with eight doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Keith Cowley had two doubles and drove in three runs and David Mallas hit a 
home run and drove in three runs for Rancho Santiago (11-2), which has won four 
consecutive conference titles. 
</P>
<P>
 Darren Troilo had three hits, including a double, and drove in a pair of two 
runs for Rancho Santiago, which has won four consecutive conference titles. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast (3-6) scored twice in the fourth to take a 2-1 lead, but Rancho 
Santiago rallied for seven runs in the fourth and three more in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Kastelic and Cowley had consecutive two-run doubles to highlight the 
fourth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore right-hander Brandon Hoalton gave up seven hits and had five 
strikeouts in eight innings for the victory, improving to 4-0 this season and 
16-0 in his career. 
</P>
<P>
 In other conference games: 
</P>
