<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: FILLMORE; 2 STABBED IN UNRELATED STREET, BAR BRAWLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bar brawl in Fillmore and a street fight in Oxnard early Saturday left two 
men with stab wounds, law enforcement officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 In Fillmore, Carlos Madrigal, 22, and a friend apparently got in an argument 
with three men inside the Santa Clara Cafe on Clay Street, Ventura County 
Sheriff's Lt. Mike Gullon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said the fight started in the bar and moved out to the alley, where 
Madrigal was stabbed in the abdomen. He was taken to Santa Paula Memorial 
Hospital for surgery and was in stable condition Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 In Oxnard, police officers responded to a call of a fight involving several 
people near Isleton Way and K Street. The crowd dispersed when police arrived, 
but officers detained several men in an alley. One of them, Manuel Barriga, 18, 
had two stab wounds and was taken to St. John's Regional Medical Center. He was 
treated and released two hours later, a nursing supervisor said. TRACY WILSON 
