HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR FREE THROWS AT 0:12 SINK 
NEWBURY PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gina Heads made a pair of free throws with 12 seconds remaining Saturday to 
lift Newport Harbor to a 43-41 victory over Newbury Park in a Southern Section 
Division III-AA semifinal game at Camarillo High. 
</P>
<P>
 Heads, who had made two of seven foul shots before the fourth quarter, tied 
the game, 41-41, on a free throw 2:38 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park (23-5) led throughout the first half, and held a 30-23 advantage 
at the break. However, Newport Harbor (22-6) held the Panthers to 11 
second-half points. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 67, Los Altos 32 -- The Indians (26-0) forced 27 turnovers en route to 
a Southern Section Division II-A playoff victory at St. Francis High. 
</P>
<P>
 Zevette Mitchell scored 16 points for Alemany, which advanced to Tuesday's 
semifinal against Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 "Tonight we played our best game since the earthquake, and if we play like 
this we should be able to win the CIF title," Coach Melissa Hearilhy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 61, Hacienda Heights 52 -- Ventura used a 27-7 run in the second half 
to overcome a 10-point deficit and win a Division II-A playoff game at Ventura 
High. Freshman guard Kristin Franklin led the Cougars with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 61, San Clemente 34 -- Buena (23-2), the No. 1 seed in Division I-A, won 
the semifinal at Rio Mesa High in Oxnard and advanced to Saturday's final 
against Santa Ana Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena's Mikko Giordano led all scorers with 16 points. MIKE GLAZE 
