<P>
 AIR BURBANK: From year to year, life doesn't change much at Burbank Airport. 
In fact, the air traffic -- air carrier, air taxi, general aviation and 
military -- hardly varied at all from 1992 to '93. . . . Overall, takeoffs and 
landings, above, went down about 2,600 flights. (B2) 
</P>
<P>
 TURF WAR: Like the drug dealers she opposes, a self-proclaimed one-woman crime 
fighter in Van Nuys is trying to protect her territory. (B1) . . . She claims a 
Neighborhood Watch group has invaded her turf and says its efforts to scare 
away prostitutes and their customers by videotaping them are ineffective. 
</P>
<P>
 FAMILY FEUDS: If you think bank robberies or murders are the most dangerous 
calls police officers face, guess again. An angry, and armed, husband and wife, 
or father and son can be much more deadly. (B1) . . . A recent FBI report said 
that domestic disturbance calls, such as the one that slain Officer Christy 
Lynne Hamilton answered in Northridge last week, account "for more line-of-duty 
deaths than any other circumstance." 
</P>
<P>
 NAME GAME: Residents of Lake Los Angeles voted in November to change the 
community's name to Desert Buttes, largely because the town no longer has a 
lake nearby. But the new name has become the butt of several jokes, including 
one that refers to residents as "butt-heads," and the local Town Council has 
scheduled another election on the issue. (B20) . . . Loyalists say the desert 
town's name is no worse than that of the Antelope Valley -- which has no 
antelopes. 
</P>
<P>
 AFTERSHOCKS: Thousands of San Fernando Valley residents affected by last 
month's Northridge earthquake are finding that it's not easy to put their lives 
back together. Many are still homeless. Others are jobless. Countless others 
have found their futures dependent on a maze of official paperwork needed for 
loans, housing, food and necessities. (B1) Burbank Flights 
</P>
<P>
 The total number of takeoffs and landings at Burbank Airport decreased 
slightly from 1992 to 1993. Totals broke down by type of aircraft: 03,18,09,09 
1992 1993 Air carrier 50,285 53,595 Air taxi 40,815 46,524 General aviation 
118,229 106,533 Military 609 673 Total 209,938 207,325 Source: 
Burbank-Glendale-Pasadena Airport Authority  
