<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIDAY'S RATING IS SECOND ONLY TO WEDNESDAY'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 helped produce the highest-rated Friday night for a network in U.S. television 
history. 
</P>
<P>
 The women's figure skating finals on CBS got a preliminary national rating of 
43.9, Nielsen Media Research said Saturday.That was 76% above two years ago, 
but 9.5% below Wednesday, the first night of women's figure skating.  
</P>
<P>
 About 4.33 million fewer homes tuned in than did on Wednesday, but the 
broadcast was still the second-highest rated night ever for the Olympics in the 
United States. Each rating point represents 942,000 homes, 1% of the television 
households in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 The previous top rating for a Friday night was 35.2. That figure was achieved 
by CBS on Nov. 21, 1980, when the "Who Shot J.R.?" episode of "Dallas" got a 
53.3 rating over one hour, and was matched by ABC on Feb. 11, 1983, when the 
"Winds of War" was televised. 
</P>
<P>
 The women's figure skating finals on CBS two years ago at Albertville, also on 
a Friday night, got a 25.0 rating and a 40 share. 
</P>
</TEXT>
