<P>
ED O'BANNON SAYS THAT HE MIGHT CONSIDER POSSIBILITIES OF DRAFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THOMAS BONK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ed O'Bannon is considering leaving UCLA and making himself available to the 
NBA draft. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Bannon, a 21-year-old junior, the Bruins' leading scorer and rebounder, said 
Saturday that he is undecided on whether to take advantage of a new NCAA rule 
that allows players to be drafted, then return to school if they do not wish to 
sign. 
</P>
<P>
 "Right now, I'm just thinking about the tournament," O'Bannon said. "If I were 
a lottery pick, maybe things would be different, but right now, leaving is not 
on my mind." 
</P>
<P>
 O'Bannon said he is leaning toward remaining at UCLA, where he is a 
pre-communications studies major. THOMAS BONK 
</P>
