<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED, 3 OTHERS INJURED IN FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman was killed and three other people were injured Saturday in an accident 
on the Ventura Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 4 p.m. on the westbound freeway near the San Diego 
Freeway interchange, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Late Saturday, California Highway Patrol officers were still investigating the 
cause of the accident in which a car carrying two women collided with a pickup 
truck and overturned, said CHP spokesman Bruce Ferrier. 
</P>
<P>
 The names of the victims were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the fatality, the accident left two adults seriously injured 
and an 8-year-old child with minor injuries, a Los Angeles Fire Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two westbound lanes of the Ventura Freeway were closed for more than four 
hours after the accident, Ferrier said. 
</P>
