<P>
SANTA ANA MAN FATALLY SHOT IN DISPUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was shot and killed after arguing with two men outside his apartment 
building, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Alfredo Orozco-Lujan, 21, was taken to a nearby hospital after the fight about 
11:30 p.m. Friday, police said, and was pronounced dead when he arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 Orozco-Lujan got into a dispute with a visitor, believed to be the assailant, 
in front of the apartment building in the 700 block of East Walnut Street, 
Santa Ana Police Cpl. Dan McDermott said. The two men may have been arguing 
because the visitor wanted to enter the apartment complex, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The visitor left after the short dispute, but returned about five minutes 
later with another man. After the three men renewed the argument, McDermott 
said, the assailant pulled out a handgun of unknown caliber, shot Orozco-Lujan 
and fled with his companion. 
</P>
<P>
 No arrests had been made Saturday. 
</P>
