<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.N. CONDEMNATION OF KILLINGS DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Security Council on Saturday postponed for a second day condemnation of 
Friday's massacre of Palestinians by an Israeli at a Hebron mosque.Disagreement 
over the text of a resolution was cited as the reason for the delay. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will make another attempt to draft a resolution Monday, diplomats 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Negotiations continued for much of Saturday among the United States, the 
Palestine Liberation Organization and diplomats from Islamic countries. 
</P>
<P>
 They agreed earlier that the council will work on a resolution, rather than 
just a statement. A resolution carries greater weight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
