<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: FULLERTON'S ROPAK REPORTS PROFIT NEARLY TRIPLED IN '93 
TO $3.5 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ropak Corp., the Fullerton maker of plastic packaging and handling products, 
reported a profit of $3.5 million, or 78 cents a share, for 1993, nearly triple 
the $1.3 million, or 30 cents a share, for 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales rose 11%, to $105.2 million from $94.8 million. For the fourth quarter, 
net income totaled $1.8 million, or 39 cents a share, which included a gain of 
$2.5 million from the exchange of a $3.5-million subordinated note issued in 
connection with an acquisition. That compares with profit of $85,000, or 2 
cents a share, recorded in the 1992 fourth quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
