<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: PICO-UNION; LOANS OFFERED FOR HOUSING REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residential property owners in the Pico-Union 1 Redevelopment Project area can 
apply for low-interest loans through the Community Redevelopment Agency to 
improve their homes or income properties. 
</P>
<P>
 The agency is providing loans at 3%, 5% and 7% interest for roof repairs, 
interior and exterior paint, new plumbing and electrical systems, new 
foundations and other repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is available to residential property owners in the area bounded by 
Olympic Boulevard on the north, the Harbor Freeway on the east, Union and 
Burlington avenues on the west and the Santa Monica Freeway on the south. 
</P>
<P>
 Property owners who apply and qualify for the loans may also be eligible to 
receive grants of up to $7,500 for exterior improvements such as landscaping, 
sprinklers and fencing. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 385-6421. 
</P>
