<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-CITY AREA; REDEVELOPMENT PLAN TO UNDERGO REVIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Portions of a draft redevelopment plan for Wilshire Center and Koreatown will 
be reviewed by a Community Redevelopment Agency citizens panel at 1 p.m. 
Thursday at Southwestern University School of Law, 675 S. Westmoreland Ave. The 
public is invited. 
</P>
<P>
 The redevelopment agency's staff will tell the Community Advisory Committee 
about the potential redevelopment and revitalization options in Wilshire Center 
and Koreatown, an area bounded by 6th Street on the north, 12th Street on the 
south and Hoover Street on the east and Western Avenue on the west. The area 
also includes the Vermont Avenue corridor to the Hollywood Freeway and Western 
Avenue to Melrose Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will include an update on the environmental review process and the 
results of a preliminary field survey of the area. 
</P>
