<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT TO STAFF RAPE HOT LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The East Los Angeles Rape Hotline needs bilingual volunteers to staff its 
24-hour hot line and help rape victims. 
</P>
<P>
 A training orientation session will be held at 6 p.m. Wednesday at Santa Marta 
Hospital, 319 N. Humphreys Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Trainees will receive 45 hours of instruction over the next two months. 
Instruction will cover the social, medical and legal aspects of rape. Trainees 
will also receive instruction on phone techniques, intervention and advocacy 
skills. 
</P>
<P>
 Avance Human Services, which runs the hot line, will also start a support 
group for battered women on Thursday.  
</P>
<P>
 Support group information: (800) 585-6231. 
</P>
<P>
 Information on volunteer training: (213) 526-5819. 
</P>
