<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO -- Start training now for the Examiner Bay to Breakers Race. The 
wacky, scenic and hugely popular 7.5-mile race from downtown to Ocean Beach is 
May 15, but registration is Tuesday through April 15.$14 fee includes T-shirt, 
pre-race health expo and post-race festival. (415) 777-7770. SAN CLEMENTE -- 
Handmade treasures, fresh produce and entertainment are featured at the Village 
Arts and Crafts Fair, 10 a.m.-4 p.m. next Sunday along Avenida Del Mar. (The 
Farmers' Market is 10 a.m.-2 p.m.) Free. (714) 361-0735. 
</P>
<P>
 LA QUINTA -- A juried show with about 200 artists is the centerpiece of the La 
Quinta Arts Festival, 10 a.m.-5 p.m. March 17-20 in La Quinta Community Park, 
Eisenhower Drive and Montezuma. $5, general; free for kids under 12. (619) 
564-1244. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO -- A floral extravaganza awaits at "Kaleidoscope of Orchids," March 
18-20 at the Scottish Rite Memorial Center, 1895 Camino del Rio South. The 48th 
annual Orchid Show and Plant Sale, with competitions, classes and displays, is 
6-10 p.m. Friday, 9 a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday, 9 a.m.-4 p.m. Sunday. $3 in advance; 
$4 at the door; free for kids under 12. Sponsored by the San Diego County 
Orchid Society. (619) 232-5762. 
</P>
<P>
 SOLVANG -- Sweet, savory and scenic, the second annual Taste of Solvang shows 
off the area's foods and sights, March 18-20. Featured: The Dessert Showcase, 
7-9 p.m. Friday at the Royal Scandinavian Inn, 400 Alisal Road ($8); the 
"Walking Smorgaasbord," 11 a.m.-4 p.m. Saturday throughout the village ($18 
includes carriage rides and a souvenir plate), and the World's Largest Danish, 
a continental breakfast with kransekage (Danish ring cake), 8-10 a.m. Sunday in 
Solvang Park ($5). $25 for weekend pass. Advance ticket purchase recommended. 
(800) 467-6582, Ext. 519. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
