<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; SAVING GRACES AT LONDON'S MUSEUMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 From Goya at the Royal Academy of Arts to Faberge at the Victoria and Albert, 
London's museums and galleries offer a visual cornucopia and for the first 
time, visitors may purchase three- and seven-day passes that allow admission to 
all two, plus 10 other participating venues and save about $60 in the process. 
</P>
<P>
 The new pass, called the "White Card," sells for just over $15 (three days) 
and $31 (seven).Family tickets are also available for up to two adults and two 
children under 17 and are about $39 for three days and $78 for seven. 
</P>
<P>
 In London, White Cards may be purchased at the participating museums and 
galleries, hotels and airlines and some Underground Stations. Ticket brokers 
Edwards and Edwards in New York City (tel. 800-223-6108) also handle the cards, 
but charge a $8-per-person booking fee. 
</P>
