<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMPLY SURREAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Claude Molveau's "My Best Shot" (Feb. 6): Salvador Dali could not 
have done it better! With its peering viewpoint, vast landscape (of a desolate 
world only "inhabited" by objects), and ethereal colors, Molveau should title 
his photograph of Monument Valley, Ariz., "The Persistence of Camera and Eye." 
</P>
<P>
 JENNIFER WILLIAMS 
</P>
<P>
 Oceanside 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
